The Arewa Youth Coalition has expressed dismay over the alleged report that some senators were planning to pass vote of no confidence on the Senate president Ahmed Lawan in order to remove him The National President of the group, Comrade Muktar Muhammad, in a statement issued to newsmen in Kaduna, called on the senators to support Lawan’s leadership as he worked towards building a better working relationship between the executive and legislature. Muhammad said the alleged impeachment move against Senate leadership was as a plot against President Muhammadu Buhari’s administration. Senate Presidency: Northern group rejects Lawan, backs Ndume APC leadership blamed for Saraki’s ordeal Again, PDP lawmakers caution against plot to remove Saraki